# Add Company to Market Map

When the user asks to add a company to the market map, follow these steps:

## Expected Input Format

The user will provide some or all of:
- **Company name** (required)
- **Sector** (required) — must be one of the valid sectors below
- **Category** (required) — must match a category within the chosen sector
- **Shortlist UUID** (required) — the company's UUID for the drops URL

## Valid Sectors and Categories

- **AI & Models**: Foundation Models, Voice & Audio, Vision & Video, AI Research, AI Tools
- **Enterprise Software**: Productivity, Operations, HR & People, Legal Tech, Hospitality
- **Consumer & Marketplace**: E-Commerce, Marketplace, Social, Lifestyle, Food & Drink
- **Developer Tools**: Dev Platforms, API & SDKs, Cloud & Infra, Networking
- **Healthcare & Biotech**: Clinical & Care, Biotech, Health Insurance, Medical Devices
- **Media & Marketing**: Advertising, Media & Content, Creator Tools, Marketing Tech
- **Hardware & Robotics**: Robotics, Vehicles & Mobility, Space, Quantum & Computing
- **Fintech**: Trading & Capital Markets, Payments & Lending, Insurance, Financial Data
- **Security & Privacy**: Cybersecurity, Privacy & Identity, AI Safety
- **Automation & Agents**: AI Agents, Conversational AI, Workflow Automation
- **Defense & Government**: Defense, Gov Tech, Policy & Research
- **Energy & Climate**: Energy, Materials & Mining

## Steps

1. Open `data/companies.json`
2. Create a new entry with this schema:
   ```json
   {
     "name": "Company Name",
     "sector": "Sector Name",
     "category": "Category Name",
     "shortlistUrl": "https://shortlistjobs.com/drops/UUID"
   }
   ```
3. Insert the entry in the correct position — group it with other companies in the same sector and category
4. Save the file

## Example Prompt

> Add company: Anthropic, AI & Models, Foundation Models, c01a830d-2457-42b0-85c5-9e3ae2d09706

## Bulk Add

Users may provide multiple companies at once. Add each one following the same rules.
